      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Are quantum computing stocks a good investment?</summary>
        <p>They offer immense upside potential but are considered high-risk, speculative investments. They are best suited for investors with a long time horizon who are comfortable with extreme volatility and the possibility that some pure-play companies may fail.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What are the best quantum computing stocks?</summary>
        <p>Investors typically choose between massive tech conglomerates (like IBM, Google, or Microsoft) that have well-funded quantum divisions but are insulated by other revenue streams, or pure-play quantum startups (like IonQ or Rigetti) that offer pure exposure but much higher risk.</p>
      </details>
